Workflow of the concept of hybrid descriptor engineering: C2DB database feeds the descriptor processing that produces input features for ML training and prediction. The generated features are mixed features from vectorized property matrices and empirical function property.

The next step is to compute property vectors based on the property matrices. We define a property vector as a set of eigenvalues that characterize the property matrix : PiX=λX\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
